  "prompt": "What is the Golden Gate bridge named after?",
  "response": "The Golden Gate Bridge is named after the Golden Gate strait, which is the narrow, mile-wide (1.6 km) channel connecting San Francisco Bay to the Pacific Ocean. The term \"Golden Gate\" was first used by John C. Fr\u00e9mont in 1846, who named it for its potential as a harbor entrance. The name predates the bridge itself by several decades. When the bridge was constructed in the 1930s, it was built across this strait, spanning from San Francisco to Marin County.",
